events.description: The Battle of Raft Swamp marks the last battle fought in North Carolina during the American Revolutionary War with a Patriot victory. It occurred four days before the British surrender at Yorktown.

events.description: The Montgolfier brothers' hot air balloon makes the first human ascent, piloted by Jean-François Pilâtre de Rozier.

events.description: Queen Marie Antoinette of France is tried and convicted of treason.
events.html: • 1793 – Queen Marie Antoinette of France is tried and convicted of treason.[6]

events.description: Napoleon begins his exile on Saint Helena in the South Atlantic Ocean.
events.html: • 1815 – Napoleon begins his exile on Saint Helena in the South Atlantic Ocean.[7]

events.description: American Civil War: The Union garrison of Glasgow, Missouri surrenders to Confederate forces.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: The Union garrison of Glasgow, Missouri surrenders to Confederate forces.

events.description: The Edison Electric Light Company begins operation.
events.html: • 1878 – The Edison Electric Light Company begins operation.

events.description: The "From Hell" letter allegedly sent by Jack the Ripper is received by investigators.
events.html: • 1888 – The "From Hell" letter allegedly sent by Jack the Ripper is received by investigators.

events.description: Airship America is launched from New Jersey in the first attempt to cross the Atlantic by a powered aircraft.
events.html: • 1910 – Airship America is launched from New Jersey in the first attempt to cross the Atlantic by a powered aircraft.

events.description: The German Rentenmark is introduced in Germany to counter hyperinflation in the Weimar Republic.
events.html: • 1923 – The German Rentenmark is introduced in Germany to counter hyperinflation in the Weimar Republic.

events.description: The airship Graf Zeppelin completes its first trans-Atlantic flight, landing at Lakehurst, New Jersey, United States.

events.description: Tata Airlines (later to become Air India) makes its first flight.
events.html: • 1932 – Tata Airlines (later to become Air India) makes its first flight.

events.description: The New York Municipal Airport (later renamed LaGuardia Airport) is dedicated.
events.html: • 1939 – The New York Municipal Airport (later renamed LaGuardia Airport) is dedicated.

events.description: President Lluís Companys of Catalonia is executed by the Francoist government.
events.html: • 1940 – President Lluís Companys of Catalonia is executed by the Francoist government.

events.description: World War II: Germany replaces the Hungarian government after Hungary announces an armistice with the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Germany replaces the Hungarian government after Hungary announces an armistice with the Soviet Union.[8]

events.description: Mexican chemist Luis E. Miramontes completes the synthesis of norethisterone, the basis of an early oral contraceptive.
events.html: • 1951 – Mexican chemist Luis E. Miramontes completes the synthesis of norethisterone, the basis of an early oral contraceptive.

events.description: Hurricane Hazel devastates the eastern seaboard of North America, killing 95 and causing massive floods as far north as Toronto.
events.html: • 1954 – Hurricane Hazel devastates the eastern seaboard of North America, killing 95 and causing massive floods as far north as Toronto.

events.description: FORTRAN, the first modern computer language, is first shared with the coding community.
events.html: • 1956 – FORTRAN, the first modern computer language, is first shared with the coding community.

events.description: Vietnam War: A draft card is burned during an anti-war rally by the Catholic Worker Movement, resulting in the first arrest under a new law.
events.html: • 1965 – Vietnam War: A draft card is burned during an anti-war rally by the Catholic Worker Movement, resulting in the first arrest under a new law.

events.description: The Black Panther Party is created by Huey P. Newton and Bobby Seale.
events.html: • 1966 – The Black Panther Party is created by Huey P. Newton and Bobby Seale.

events.description: During the construction of Australia's West Gate Bridge, a span of the bridge falls and kills 35 workers. The incident is the country's worst industrial accident to this day.
events.html: • 1970 – During the construction of Australia's West Gate Bridge, a span of the bridge falls and kills 35 workers. The incident is the country's worst industrial accident to this day.[9]

events.description: Supporters of the Malta Labour Party ransack and destroy the Times of Malta building and other locations associated with the Nationalist Party.
events.html: • 1979 – Supporters of the Malta Labour Party ransack and destroy the Times of Malta building and other locations associated with the Nationalist Party.

events.description: A coup d'état in El Salvador overthrows President Carlos Humberto Romero and begins the 12 year-long Salvadoran Civil War.
events.html: • 1979 – A coup d'état in El Salvador overthrows President Carlos Humberto Romero and begins the 12 year-long Salvadoran Civil War.[10]

events.description: Aero Trasporti Italiani Flight 460 crashes near Conca di Crezzo, Italy, killing all 37 people on board.
events.html: • 1987 – Aero Trasporti Italiani Flight 460 crashes near Conca di Crezzo, Italy, killing all 37 people on board.[11]

events.description: A coup d'état in Burkina Faso overthrows and kills then President Thomas Sankara.

events.description: Wayne Gretzky becomes the all-time leading points scorer in the NHL.
events.html: • 1989 – Wayne Gretzky becomes the all-time leading points scorer in the NHL.

events.html: • 1990 – Soviet Union leader Mikhail Gorbachev is awarded the Nobel Peace Prize for his efforts to lessen Cold War tensions and open up his nation.
